INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
========================

Elegant Functional Programming Library v0.0.1

## Quick Installation

For most systems, the standard autotools installation process works:

    ./configure
    make
    make check
    sudo make install
    sudo ldconfig    # On Linux systems

## Prerequisites

- C99-compatible compiler (GCC, Clang)
- GNU Autotools (autoconf, automake, libtool)
- GNU make
- Standard C library and libm (math library)

### Installing Prerequisites

Ubuntu/Debian:
    sudo apt-get install build-essential autoconf automake libtool

CentOS/RHEL/Fedora:
    sudo yum install gcc autoconf automake libtool
    # or on newer versions:
    sudo dnf install gcc autoconf automake libtool

macOS (with Homebrew):
    brew install autoconf automake libtool

## Configuration Options

    --enable-debug          Enable debug mode with memory tracking
    --enable-examples       Build example programs
    --prefix=PREFIX         Install to PREFIX [/usr/local]
    --libdir=DIR           Install libraries to DIR [PREFIX/lib]
    --includedir=DIR       Install headers to DIR [PREFIX/include]

## Development Installation

For development work with full debugging:

    ./configure --enable-debug --enable-examples --prefix=$HOME/local
    make
    make check
    make install

## Cross-Platform Notes

### Linux
Standard installation works on all major distributions.

### macOS
Use Homebrew or MacPorts to install autotools, then standard build.

### Windows (MSYS2/MinGW-w64)
Install MSYS2, then install build tools:
    pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-gcc mingw-w64-x86_64-autotools
    ./configure
    make

### FreeBSD/OpenBSD
Install autotools from ports/packages, then standard build.

## Post-Installation

### Verify Installation

    pkg-config --modversion elegant
    pkg-config --cflags --libs elegant

### Test Installation

Create a simple test program:

    #include <elegant.h>
    int main() {
        AUTO(arr, elegant_create_array_int(1, 2, 3));
        return 0;
    }

Compile and run:
    gcc test.c $(pkg-config --cflags --libs elegant) -o test
    ./test

## Uninstallation

    sudo make uninstall

## Troubleshooting

### Missing autotools
Install autoconf, automake, and libtool for your platform.

### Build failures
Try a clean rebuild:
    make distclean
    ./configure [options]
    make

### Permission errors during installation
Use sudo for system-wide installation or install to a user directory:
    ./configure --prefix=$HOME/local

### Library not found at runtime
Update library path:
    sudo ldconfig                    # Linux
    export DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=...    # macOS
    export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=...      # Other Unix

## Support

For build issues, check:
- That you have all prerequisites installed
- That you're using a supported compiler
- The configure output for any error messages

For more information, see README.md and docs/overview.md.
